sms and active sites, promotors and poisons in redox and acid-base catalysis. This advanced textbook is recommended for Master and PhD students, for whom it provides the fundamentals and all relevant aspects of catalyst synthesis, characterization and application in suitable reactors. It is not only thermal catalysis that is covered in depth, but also photo- and electrocatalysis as emerging fields in the Energiewende.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCatalysis. 4aHeterogene Katalyse. 4aKatalysator. 4aKatalyse. 4aOberflächenchemie. 7aSCIENCE / Chemistry / Physical & Theoretical.2bisacsh  aCatalysis.  aCatalyst.  aHeterogeneous Catalysis.  aPhysical Chemistry.  aSurface Chemistry.1 aKleist, Wolfgang, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMuhler, Martin, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2023 Englishz978311131923008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2023z9783111318660oZDB-23-DPC0 cEPUBz97831106325450 cprintz978311063247740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311063248440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110632484423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110632484/original  a978-3-11-117578-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  a978-3-11-131923-0  EBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKA